{
  "texts": [
    "Potential topics of future research include:",
    "• Student perceptions of the use of AI in assessment (del Gobbo et al., 2023);",
    "• How to make data more secure (Ullrich et al., 2022);",
    "• How to correct sample bias and balance issues of privacy with the affordances of AI (Saghiri et al., 2022; Zhang et al., 2023); and • How institutions are storing and using teaching and learning data (Ifenthaler & Yau, 2020; Maphosa & Maphosa, 2021; McConvey et al., 2023; Rangel-de Lázaro & Duart, 2023; Sghir et al., 2022; Ullrich et al., 2022).",
    "Aside from recognising that further empirical research is needed (e.g., Alkhalil et al., 2021; Buchanan et al., 2021), more rigorous reporting of study design in primary research was called for, including ensuring that the number of participants and study level is reported (Fichten et al., 2021; Harmon et al., 2021)."
  ]
}